<br>
You got me all wrong.  I haven't helped anyone with their Ragefire because I haven't had any free time.  We raid almost every day, and non-raid days are spent concentrating on exp or helping guildmates get their epics (not clerics).<br>
<br>
I would love to help other clerics get their epics because I do not have mine and I know how important it is to a cleric and their guild.  However, I don't see this as a possibility for me until I get level 60 with a nice raid buffer of exp.<br>
<br>
My problem with a list (which is what Wolvar is advocating) is the inefficiency it promotes.  Our server crashes way too often to allow any wasted time on Ragefire kills.  A list is not the right solution.  In fact, in the current environment of the Tribunal, we (everyone) are killing Ragefire at peak efficiency.  There is no compelling reason to change that.<br>
<br>
Bowynn,<br>
<br>
A level 45 cleric trying to kill Ragefire is a possibility if you imagine the Tribunal in Wolvar's fantasy world.  He wants to control the spawn by the force of many guilds working together to shut out those who do not submit to his will.<br>
<br>
It all comes down to his hatred and envy of larger guilds.  He wants to reap the benefits of being in an uber-guild without the hard work that goes into building such a guild.  A few paragraphs ago, I mentioned the amount of time that EV spends raiding.  We raid so often that our non-raid days *must* be spent exp camping or members will begin to lose more exp than they gain.  This is the hard work that makes us an uber guild.<br>
<br>
Epics are not rewards in and of themselves.  They are tools that enable us to hunt in new zones and fight the mightiest MoBs in the game.  This is why Ragefire must die as soon as possible every time he spawns.  Adding an artificial bottleneck to the cleric epic is a horrible idea. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uteadain.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Teadain</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/1/01 2:00:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire</span><hr size=1> Jesus you guys are incredible. Its like if you guys can find a reason to argue and yell back and forth so be it. Any guild that takes ragefire from a cleric camping him for multiple hours with his/her guild otw, you guys are just a bunch of heartless assholes. I wouldnt allow my guild to do it but all your actions do on this game is show a reflection of your personality in RL. <br>
