In an ideal scenario there would be some sort of list devised by the clerics with the pearl. Taking the Luclin server as an example it could be done in a like fashion. A list could be formed by cleric name not guild name. Clerics on the whole would be in agreement and aware of the list order. Ragefire pops and the next in line starts to assemble. Anyone and everyone with the time to assist does so. We all go when its spoken across our guild chat if able. Should the next cleric in line not BE online next in place goes and so on but again leaving the cleric who didnt happen to be online up for the next spawn. Theres a line to kill him of clerics not guilds. When a clerics turn is up the server assists with those able to go. Grey areas would be things like the cleric not online having 30 minutes to be contacted via phone or whatever means to get online before being set back a turn. Ideally there would be no wait time if the server post 50's were aware of just killing Ragefire for somebody not a certain somebody. Everyone has sufficient force at any hour should they be on when their turn comes. This is jarbled idealism as its late and I shoulda been asleep but great sex wakes me up and I needed a smoke. Oops off topic sorry. Anyway idealistically we all work on the list together helping each cleric in line kill Ragefire. This is an idealism that can be altered and tinkered with but the "unsaid" ideal for us all to ponder. *waits for laughter*<br>
<br>
<br>
Now given the current environment its no more greedy, as its been said on both accounts, to have the numbers to kill when the cleric camped in lair doesnt then it is for that cleric sitting there without a snowballs chance in hell of getting the team ready within a couple hours. This is exaggerated at times but can and will happen so who's greedy? The cleric knowing they dont have enough sitting on their ass for an item rather than assisting guildmates elsewhere or the group going in with a cleric in force balls to the wall ready to go and saying "sorry we are taking the spawn"? Again slightly exaggerated but thats the arguement here. I for one am a person if asked willing to go and help, so call on me as well. I cant say I will ditch my current responsibilities to my own guild to do so though just because somebody wants an epic. Everyone does. I dont like FCFS/FFA personally but will compete and will be as respectful as those I compete against deserve.<br>
<br>
<br>
The responses to Wolvars post were hysterical. What a bunch of jackasses. Read it again shitheads. He didnt say lets all fuck over the ubers. He includes anyone and everyone WILLING to do basically the ideal above. Everyone gets together and gets it done for whoever. Whether your KoT, SP, E/V, or any other guild on the server. He didnt say E/V wouldnt be a part of it he said those who werent or didnt wish to be a part of helping everyone wouldnt sign up to any sort of list. <br>
<br>
