</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#4D4D4D><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uboinshar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Boinshar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>n00b</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(6/3/01 10:31:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Ragefire</span><hr size=1> Details people, details.<br>
<br>
It's nice to suggest a list without even pretending to come up with guidelines for it. Idealism at it's best, eh?<br>
<br>
Personally I'm tired of racing to Ragefire, and I would more than welcome a list system. However, unless someone take the time and effort to hammer out details and get everyone to agree, it's all hot air atm. For a list to work, the following have to be observed:<br>
<br>
-What level does a cleric has to be in order to be on the list? (Some would say 51, others 56, and still others 60's first)<br>
-How do you determine the order? level based? random rolls?<br>
-Who's going to camp there all day for Ragefire? The next person on the list? or some volunteer?<br>
-Who's in charge of notification, and who's keeping track of when Rage spawns? If Rage spawns at 9AM EST, I'm sure someone can take him down without anyone else knowing about it.<br>
-Last but not least, how in god's name do you enforce it? An agreement only works until the first time it's broken, then all hell breaks loose.<br>
<br>
I'd support a list system if someone's willing to take the time and effort to set it into motion. I just highly doubt it's going to happen. <br>
<br>
If someone wish to spend 30 hours to camp a spawn, they deserve it just because of their persistance and patience. If two or more people are camping it, roll for it. There's no reason to step on other people's toes to get to Ragefire. If someone has a legit claim on Ragefire, you can count on me to help with taking him down.<br>
<br>
Speaking of legit claims, the rules and etiquette have changed. What exact are we doing now? Whoever gets 2 groups into SS? or Whichever cleric who was camping Rage when it spawns? or Whoever can muster enough people under 30 minutes? or Whoever hands in the pearl?<br>
<br>
Boinshar<br>
